[[Cornwall Council]] in [[England]] is elected every four years. From 1973 to 2005 elections were for Cornwall [[County Council]], with the first election for the new [[Unitary authority|unitary]] Cornwall Council held in June 2009. This election saw 123 members elected, replacing the previous 82 councillors on Cornwall County Council and the 249 on the six district councils.<ref>[http://www.cornwall.gov.uk/default.aspx?page=17444 Cornwall Council June 2009 Electoral divisions]</ref>
